We used to eat at the pub once a week. The menu was great and food was always super tasty. Anything we would order always tasted great. The deserts were scrumptious!
We visited the pub again after a month of being away and found that the menu has changed and was only a fraction of what it used to be and not that much choice any more. The food was definitely worse than ever before. However, the deserts were the biggest disappointment. From something that was irresistible to something more like unedible. There was four of us and each ordered a different desert. The fruit tarts were soggy rather than with a nice crunchy base, sticky toffi pudding was dry and hard at the bottom, obviously microwaved, apple pie again all soggy. Everything was microwaved. Sadly after years of going there we won't be coming back. The only good thing about this place is still their great service. Shout of to the lady that's always there looking after the customers best she can! 5*

We chose from the lunchtime menu, for which there is a separate gluten free menu available. You are also able to order from the main menu. Fries aren't available on the NCIG menu as they cook them in a fryer that has come into contact with items that do contain gluten, so mum could have ordered them as a side off the main menu if she wanted to.

My biggest bugbear was that I ordered the feta flat bread, which should have had humous, avocado, pomegranate, olives and lambs lettuce. Part way through, I realised there was no avocado or pomegranate at all! When I mentioned this to the waitress, she checked with the chef and they didn't have any! If I had been given that information, I would have opted for the steak sandwich, but by then it was too late.

In all fairness, the waitress was lovely about it and I think the chef may have had a little telling off, but of course common sense should have prevailed! The desserts were lovely! Again, the raspberry coulis and strawberries accompanying mum's cheesecake were missing, but the waitress noticed and brought some fresh raspberries out, at least!

A bit more thought and it could be really good!
